    <abstract id="aspace_1067473ca4fbe421a265392bd3921ffe">Located in Milton, Mass.  Grew out of classes at Boston University under the direction of Dr. Samuel Silas Curry begun in 1879.  Separated from the university in 1884.  Originally know as the School of Expression.  At about the same time Anna Baright (later married to Curry) organized the School of Elocution and Expression.  The two schools merged in 1883.  Incorporated in 1888.  Dr. Curry died in 1921 and Anna Curry died in 1923.  Alumni took control of the school in Nov. 1924 and began calling it the Curry School of Expression.  In 1938 school was granted power to award BS and MS in Oratory, at which point the school was called Curry.  It officially became Curry College in 1943.  Absorbed Perry Normal School in 1974.</abstract>
